sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: MB-RFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Mammalian-Bacterial promoter with RFP reporter: CArG promoter sequence + BBaK216005 + BBa_K08101
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Our hybrid promoter hopes to add to the systems already in the registry by creating a hybrid promoter that combines the bacterial promoter PyeaR and the mammalian CArG element , in the orientation mammalian to bacterial, both of which respond to exogenous nitrogenous species. Combining the two would allow a more modular NO sensor that can be used in mammalian and bacterial cells interchangeably. The hybrid promoter has been attached to the reporter: Red Fluorescent Protein (RFP). The hybrid promoter has been characterised by observing expression of flourescent protein, and found to have increased transcription in response to increasing concentrations of potassium nitrate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: NRP-UEA-Norwich
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: E9-ns2 CArG promoter sequence + BHN + BBaK216005 + BBa_K081014

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K081014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
PoPS in -> RFP out
Strong RBS (efficiency=0.6).
Artificial 39 bp terminator (efficiency=0.99).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Lorenzo Pasotti, Paolo Magni

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B1006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Artificial terminator, estimated %T~>90% *8bp stem, 6nt loop *Bidirectional, estimated reverse %T~>90%
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Haiyao Huang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: modified E. coli thr terminator, replaced all A-T pairs in stem with C-G pairs
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Bidirectional, with the reverse estimated to be less effective than the forward. Has a polyA tail of 9 residues.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: M-B
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Mammalian-Bacterial Promoter: E9-ns2 CArG promoter sequence + BHN + BBaK216005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: A hybrid of the PyeaR promoter (BBaK216005) and the E9-ns2 CArG promoter (Ref1). Two versions will be synthesised, with the promoters altering their position in relation to the 5???-end of the sequence.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: NRP-UEA-Norwich
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
PyeaR promoter (BBaK216005) and the E9-ns2 CArG promoter (Ref1)
Ref1: Scott, S.D., Joiner, M.C. & Marples, B., 2002. Optimizing radiation-responsive gene promoters for radiogenetic cancer therapy. Gene therapy, 9(20), p.1396-402. Available at: http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12365005 [Accessed June 24, 2012].
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
To provide additional restriction enzyme sites that may become useful during later cloning steps, BamHI, HindIII and NdeI have been added between the 2 promoters.
It is envisaged that any open reading frame (e.g. RFP or GFP) will be cloned ???downstream??? (i.e. at the 3???-end) of these promoter sequences.
